caption: Ordered Grubhub and got dinner from here. Food was great and super delicious! Unfortunately delivery was over 1.5 hours but I’d definitely order from here again!
The meals and service were above my expectations. I really liked the environment of this restaurant. Extraordinary restaurant to take the family out for lunch.

I don’t know why people put bad reviews. I have delivery with Uber eats and it’s actually really good food and came hot. Only reason I gave four stars is because I got sweet and sour chicken and I wish it was a bit sweeter ! Other than that the food is great ☺️

We love going out. Last night we came to this excellent place which friends recommended to us. We passed a delightful evening there with high-qulity meal and a well-trained team and an impressive cook. We put this place in our phone list  and we shall surely return soon.  Highly recommended.
Pay attention to detail what it says in menu is not exactly what you get.  When you order rolls that is
Great food and service
Great sushi!
Awesome
Great food but tonight the restaurant was super cold...
attentive waiter clean comfortable tasteful good sushi I like pretty much everything
Great food. Poor service.
You need to try the pineapple fried rice! And their general tso is hands down the best I've had in Boston so far.

Food is fine but delivery is wildly unpredictable. Took 2 hours to deliver 10 minutes away this time. Sometimes it is fast, occasionally it is absurdly slow. Driver showed up an hour after quoted delivery window with 0 apology, just smiled handed food and left. Very odd experience.
Still great
Really great experience!  The Ramen was amazing tonight!
So good! I love the ramen!
Amazing
Good sushi

Better than expected. We had ramen there. While not a traditional ramen, their soup tasted better than expected. Pretty good actually. They use thin somen noodles and the combos not common among ramen places. Like seafood, beef or chicken or mapo tofu ...., instead of the general soyu and etc type.

So, i originally wanted cheaper sushi at Ebisuya but they were too busy. Went here and didnt want to pay double or triple the price so we got ramen.  I think i saw the menu saying that it's handpulled??? It definitely doesn't seem like it's handpulled. Not a big issue.  The ramen werent bad but i wish there was more meat. My bowl of R02 spicy ramen only had 2 extremely thin slice of ramen, half a egg, and little veggies. Okay for the price though. Only $10. It didnt taste bad and i actually liked it but it could be a bit more spicier.  Service was good. The host is also the waitress. She came to check on us 3x and offered help on what to order when we weren't decided yet. Nice lady  Bill comes with fortune cookies

Ordered the food for take out! It came on time and fresh which was a plus. The maki combo was relatively good. I’d definitely order it again. However, the mapo tofu ramen was subpar at best. The broth is lacking depth and wasn’t even spicy. They also don’t use the chewy curly ramen noodles so the texture wasn’t what I was expecting. Perhaps I’d just stick to sushi next time!

The reason for the 3 stars is the service provided from staff. Completely dismissive. The whole interaction was awkward and out of place. Good service is mayor key to succeed in this industry. I do have to say that the food here is great. Had no complaints with food and presentation. But in my personal opinion...great food and great/good service goes hand in hand.

The food I ordered was always on time. Also, for the price you pay you get good sushi. Try out thier food for all deal. It's pretty worth it too. Thier pork fried rice, sushi and ramens are their highlight meals according to me.
Nice place for a friendly gathering or night date out. Great food with good price. Great servers too.

Been here a couple of times and was a good experience each time. The ramen is fairly good, and the sushi was okay. The atmosphere is cozy, and does have nice space from other customers so it feels like a a private dining experience.  Also the portion sizes are pretty good for the prices and the staff is pretty attentive.

I ordered the sashimi appetizer, the philly rolls and miso soup small. Everything was very good quality and quantity, miso soup was perfect temperature. Perfect amount of soy sauce for food. Order was delivered exactly in time frame quoted on grub hub. Id definitely recommend!! Thanks guys!
Very bad and tasteless ramen.
I think we went a little too early. The tea was just hot water and the broth for my ramen was not fatty or tasty. I may have to try one of the Chinese meals. But don't go for ramen

This is the only Asian restaurant I've ever ordered from that didn't provide rice with an entree order of General Tso's Chicken. I would have added a side of white rice had I known, but this has never been an issue before with any other restaurant. Just mentioning this in case it might help someone else with their order. You do NOT get rice included with entrees, so if you want rice, make sure to add it to your order.
Bland ramen should be in the name of this place. Waste of UberEats.
Fresh and Delicious.  Tough to decide between sushi, ramen and Chinese...all looked scrumptious
Very good. The ramen is super tasty. A great quick lunch and dinner place

Delicious ramen broth and the noodles are perfect. My two favorite elements of the soup. But sadly the pork belly was dry and not rendered probably. Also I'm not a fan of plastic bowls.  But overall good service, nice ambiance, and great soup. On a final note it was incredibly easy to get here from 93 north!

So this is a review pertaining to my experience with a grubhub order. I'll say right off the bat that it's unfortunate I am giving this review because my experience wasn't all bad.  I ordered a chirashi (raw fish) meal combo w/ miso soup and a can of Coca Cola on the side. Within literally thirty minutes of putting the order in it arrived! I was pleasantly surprised and rushed out to meet the delivery driver. Upon opening up the order and getting down to business. A nice cold coke, a nice hot miso, and what's this? A warmer than room temp sashimi dish. WARMER THAN ROOM TEMP. Like, warm to the point where you poke the caviar and it's congealed together.  I did my best to eat it because I don't want to waste anything but I really couldn't. Rarely do I call a restaurant as well for a refund, if there's something wrong I usually just eat the cost because I know how it is running restaurants, I've been in and out of the industry for almost a decade.  They told me that the only way they would refund me is if they came back and took all the food away. The whole thing, coke soup and all. I tried to explain that I was already eating the soup and drinking the coke and that if they bring it back they're going to throw it away. He wouldn't have it and got very angry with me, they NEEDED all of it, half drank coke and all. Probably because he thinks I'm lying. Come on. A first time customer, at least trust someone sometimes maybe they'll come back.  So, alright, I told him I'd just call grub hub. They ended up calling the restaurant and tried to explain the situation and work something out but he refused to refund me and told me that unless I give them back EVERYTHING that I'm basically out of luck.  So, the grubhub employee apologized for the unreasonableness of the management and they gave me a $10 credit, which is okay. I really am more okay with that, because I didn't really want to take money away from the restaurant. If they could've compromised and refunded just the fish, or half the bill I would probably be leaving at least a 4-star review but due to the stubborn, angry, and very selfish management I will never recommend this place.  Bummer too, the soup is great :P
Food was awesome crab ragoon and the rice were the best will definitely go again
Fast delivery and excellent customer service
We love this place but my fried rice with lobster sauce was a bit watery and bland this time. Awesome crab rangoon s though!! Better luck on our next visit.
Surprising tasty

Went here for the first time on a whim, without having heard of Nagoya until we walked by on a shopping trip. The restaurant is decorated beautifully and is nice and clean. Our server was attentive, and the food came out quickly. Most of all, they have DELICIOUS ramen! I highly recommend the katsu ramen.

Came here mid day on a Saturday. Prompt and friendly service. I had the yakiniku ramen and it was fantastic. The meat had a nice texture, broth was excellent and spicy, and the egg was perfect. Definitely coming back here!

Food is seasoned well and is fresh. Some of the best Wonton Soup and Crab Rangoons I've had in the RI/MA area.  General T was also a very good plate.  Fried Rice is more of a sticky rice thatst fried (very good).  Girlfriend liked her Sushi rolls, I even ate some though I normally don't. Seriously try this place out!
Nice food

I was not impressed with the food here. I'm surprised this place has pretty good reviews but I felt like it didn't live up to the expectation. I came here around 2 on a weekend and they had no customer in the restaurant. Waitress was too busy talking to the other staff to take our order. When we got our food I was very disappointed. My salad came out soggy because it was soaked in dressing. my maki rolls was mosty rice and pieces of fish was so tiny.
My spring rolls were pure oil. It was really bad.
I liked the pork katsu, however the terriyaki chicken ramen was on the bland side and not very flavorful. We were the only table and had to ask to be brought water. The service was otherwise good.

I'm never the type of person to give a review but Nagoya was the best experience for ramen. I went to many sushi, japanese and ramen places only one place I go to on a regular basis but Nagoya was amazing. I'll definitely come back hopefully regularly. The atmosphere was very warming and my waitress was absolutely sweet, I wish I remembered her name. Like I said very nice and warm atmosphere, soft music was played when I was there for my whole meal

Excellent food, shrimp biryani and aloo baigan (potatoes and eggplant), and pakora to start. Reasonable prices. Nice and clean.  I'm a local paleface but native eaters drove a distance to eat here. The people working here are sweet, but you may have to ask for a fish or napkins or cutlery. ;) They're on grub hub.

I tried out Nagoya for the first time recently after seeing it on the food for all app. I got a really delicious veggie ramen loaded with a variety of vegetables and super flavorful and I think it only cost about $6 on the app- you don’t get a much better deal than that! I’m looking forward to going back, will probably become a regular spot.
It wasn't the worst ramen I've ever had but you can get better from a frozen bowl at the grocery store.
Offers both Chinese and Japanese menu. Expect fusion style and creativity, not traditional authentic Japanese style.
Good food and service
Delicious food and friendly people
Best ramen! I got the spicy pork and it was delicious. Sauce came separate than ingredients when delivered so nothing was soggy. Also had the chicken wings and crab Rangoon. Both good as well.
We had great service here and we're even able to use the Food For All app to get it a bit cheaper. lovely ramen!!
Nagoya is excellent. Always great food.

I'll come back. Came around 1:30 pm and we ordered two entrees (ramen and teriyaki) along with an appetizer. Appetizer wasn't very big but was enough for us: he loved his ramen (bit spicy and he was chugging water but thought it was delicious) and I enjoyed my teriyaki beef, though it was a little bland and could have used more sauce. Place is well air conditioned and my food got cold before I finished but I'm a slow eater. Otherwise the food gets an A from me.  The sit down area itself is small but we were the only ones there for the majority of our visit. As a result the waiter was hovering quite a bit and had some difficulty understanding our order (he didn't seem to know the whole menu yet) but the place is from what I understand pretty new. It deserves some more attention.
Great food
The gyoza was good but not amazing. The ramen wasn't bad but the soup lacked a depth of flavor I was expecting from a tonkatsu base. The pork and egg was good but poorly presented.
Amazing fresh home made ramen noodles
Good food but not much sitting, served complimentery appitizers.

I was in the area, looking for somewhere to eat and decided to try this place. I'm glad I did! Great food, large menu selection,  reasonable prices, and very friendly service. I will definitely be coming back!

The salt and pepper tofu is not on the menu but it was easy to ask for this as a substitute for the shrimp version. The chef clearly knows how to cook food from the south of China. The dish is absolutely fantastic. The ramen is more like a Chinese noodle soup than Japanese style ramen. The gyoza are excellent as well. Nagoya is a welcome addition to Medford Square.
Really good spicy tuna and eel/avocado rolls.  Great prices and better than Blue Fuji in my opinion!
Fresh sushi that's priced about right. Good selection of alternative Asian food if you have someone who isn't fond of sushi with you. Can't wait to come back and try the different special rolls.

Nagoya serves Japanese and Chinese food. A talented chef created delicious sushi with unique twists. I really enjoyed the Honey Moon roll with the delicate spice of wasabi sauce and the cooling effect of mango.  Nagoya also serves their own special style pork broth based ramen and various other Japanese and Americanized Chinese food. Booster seats and high chairs available and a very friendly staff. They will deliver too.
